      "writtenOn": "2020-10-06T03:13:32Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I have concerns whenever I see hard-coded versions like this. Is it possible to generalize this differently? Otherwise, this becomes harder for people to upgrade in the future.",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 37,
        "startChar": 33,
        "endLine": 37,
        "endChar": 40
      },
      "revId": "5064f2ed16d4bd9fa10208d1a20977c81e8bad5e",
      "serverId": "85c56323-6fa9-3386-8a01-6480fb634889"
    },
    {
      "unresolved": true,
      "key": {
        "uuid": "4eda1b59_c9c4ed47",
        "filename": "soong/clangprebuilts.go",
        "patchSetId": 1
      },
      "lineNbr": 37,
      "author": {
        "id": 1344584
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-10-06T05:43:37Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "The easiest (for me:-) would be to make clang prebuilts (supplied by llvm-toolchain build) to have prebuilts/clang/host/\u003cos\u003e/\u003cversion\u003e/lib64 contain libxml2.so symlink pointing to the specific libxml2 version (just as, say, there is libc++.so-\u003elibc++.so.1 there). However, I have no idea where such symlink should be set in llvm-toolchain build.",
      "parentUuid": "a9f98fe3_4622a61b",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 37,
        "startChar": 33,
        "endLine": 37,
        "endChar": 40
      },
      "revId": "5064f2ed16d4bd9fa10208d1a20977c81e8bad5e",
      "serverId": "85c56323-6fa9-3386-8a01-6480fb634889"
    },
    {
      "unresolved": true,
      "key": {
        "uuid": "0722227b_69b07787",
        "filename": "soong/clangprebuilts.go",
        "patchSetId": 1
      },
      "lineNbr": 37,
      "author": {
        "id": 1058860
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-10-06T05:52:24Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Note that while the symlinks do exist, we still hardcode the symlink target names rather than the link name.  I don\u0027t think a libxml2 symlink will help us here.\n\nLooks like Soong checks this file/module only if LLVM_BUILD_HOST_TOOLS is set.  So this can only cause breakages when clang-tools branch\u0027s compiler gets udpated.  I\u0027d have been more worried if this were not the case and Soong always failed if this file doesn\u0027t exist.  That\u0027d make updating libxml2 harder vis-a-vis the aosp-master-plus-llvm.",
      "parentUuid": "4eda1b59_c9c4ed47",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 37,
        "startChar": 33,
        "endLine": 37,
        "endChar": 40
      },
      "revId": "5064f2ed16d4bd9fa10208d1a20977c81e8bad5e",
      "serverId": "85c56323-6fa9-3386-8a01-6480fb634889"
    },
    {
      "unresolved": true,
      "key": {
        "uuid": "2126e4ba_cab81332",
        "filename": "soong/clangprebuilts.go",
        "patchSetId": 1
      },
      "lineNbr": 37,
      "author": {
        "id": 1344584
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-10-06T16:33:31Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "\u003e I don\u0027t think a libxml2 symlink will help us here.\nIf I manually create libxml2.so-\u003elibxml2.so.2.9.10 link in `prebuilts/clang/host/linux-x86/clang-r399163b/lib64` and set `libxml2soName` to \"libxml2.so\" in clangprebuilts.go, `prebuilts/clang-tools/build-prebuilts.sh` succeeds, because Soong is happy as libxml2.so file exists, so it can proceed, and the name of the libxml2 library in out/soong/dist/linux-x86/lib64 (which will become prebuilts/clang-tools/linux-x86/lib64 after checkin) is automatically corrected by the post-build phase of build-prebuilts.sh script to libxml2.so.2.9.10 (https://cs.android.com/android/platform/superproject/+/master:development/vndk/tools/header-checker/android/build-prebuilts.sh;drc\u003df1036391fc9de0553124815ff519191dc7ac588c;l\u003d113)\n\nI haven\u0027t verified this approach for Darwin, but I hope it will work there, too.",
      "parentUuid": "0722227b_69b07787",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 37,
        "startChar": 33,
        "endLine": 37,
        "endChar": 40
      },
      "revId": "5064f2ed16d4bd9fa10208d1a20977c81e8bad5e",
      "serverId": "85c56323-6fa9-3386-8a01-6480fb634889"
    },
    {
      "unresolved": true,
      "key": {
        "uuid": "52afc102_dc5c088d",
        "filename": "soong/clangprebuilts.go",
        "patchSetId": 1
      },
      "lineNbr": 37,
      "author": {
        "id": 1058860
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-10-06T17:01:47Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Back when I wrote this code, IIRC, soong wasn\u0027t copying the symlink targets to the install directory.  If that\u0027s no longer the case, I agree this will work.  (Need to verify on Darwin like you mentioned.)\n\nIn the toolchain build (out/lib/libxml2-linux-install), this symlink is already present.  So we can change the toolchain build scripts to package the symlink.  Given that\u0027d require new prebuilts, let\u0027s submit this change to unblock the kzip build and remove the hardcoded version after the next prebuilt update.",
      "parentUuid": "2126e4ba_cab81332",
